cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NI 

This paper deals with detecting attacks in cyber-physical systems using supervised regression, which is a common approach in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of learning approaches to stealthy attacks, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of game theory to model the interaction between the defender and attacker suggests that it may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on sensor readings and physical damage suggests that it may belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
